Commands and assumptions:


Kubectl commands to deploy the services:
-----------------------------------------
kubectl create -f deployment.yml --namespace namespace_name
kubectl create -f configmap.yml --namespace namespace_name
kubectl create -f ingress.yml --namespace namespace_name
kubectl create -f service.yml --namespace namespace_name




Assumptions made:
-------------------

- Few of the assumptions is defined in the docker file as we are creating the image out of the docker file. 
- Assume kubernetes cluster is installed already. 


I do not have a great experience with prometheus and grafana before. I will use some online help as below to make sure the integration works and displays all the logs.

https://sysdig.com/blog/kubernetes-monitoring-prometheus/
https://grafana.com/grafana/dashboards/315